    <text>
        <body>
            <div1 type="calendarCollection">
                <!--div1 just wraps the whole collection. -->


                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-01-30"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/february/1909-01-30.jpg">

                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP
                        CALENDAR CO. NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab rend="print" hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-01-30"> January 30, 1909. <lb/>Saturday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure rend="cutout" hand="#blackpen">
                        <figDesc resp="#acolemanreeves"> A man with a <rs type="object"
                                >mustache</rs> lying in <rs type="object">bed</rs>. </figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil" rend="cursive"> E.R.B. <lb/>"That damned old <rs
                            type="object">clock</rs>
                        <lb/>gives me a shock<lb/>
                        Each morning when it’s dark<lb/>
                        <emph style="underline">It likes</emph> the fun, but I’ve begun<lb/>
                        To tire of the lark!”
 
                    </ab>
                </div2>


                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-02-16"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/february/1909-02-16.jpg">

                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP
                        CALENDAR CO. NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab rend="print" hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-02-16"> February 16, 1909. <lb/>Tuesday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure rend="color" hand="#multicolor">
                        <figDesc resp="#acolemanreeves">
                            <persName>Mr Behrend</persName> holding a large <rs type="animal"
                                >bug.</rs>
                        </figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil" rend="cursive">
                        <persName>Mr. Behrend</persName> finds a <lb/> <rs type="animal">bed bug</rs>!</ab>
                    <ab hand="#redPen" rend="cursive"> I wonder if you have found many lately?</ab>
                </div2>




                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-02-17"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/february/1909-02-17.jpg">

                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP
                        CALENDAR CO. NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-02-17">February 17, 1909. <lb/>Wednesday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc resp="#acolereeves"/>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil" rend="#cursive">
                        <lb/> Each morning <emph style="underline">very</emph> early <lb/> When all is dark and still<lb/>
                        <persName>Ernst</persName> goes <emph style="underline">off</emph> in inky blackness <lb/>To work at
                            <rs type="location">Hammermill</rs>
                        <lb/> I really think he's <emph style="underline">very</emph> good <lb/>to get up when it’s dark <lb/>
                        For tho’ he <emph style="underline">says</emph> he doesn’t mind <lb/> 
                        It can't be such a <emph style="underline">lark!</emph> </ab>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" place="bottom-right">Poor thing! is it still
                            dark when you arise?</add></ab>
                </div2>



                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-08"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/march/1909-03-08.jpg">

                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP
                        CALENDAR CO. NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-08">March 8, 1909. <lb/>Monday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#redink">
                        <figDesc resp="#acolemanreeves">A large <rs type="object">question mark</rs>
                            in the center of the paper.</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" place="bottom-right">Perhaps this is <emph style="underline">the</emph> day,
                            tho’ I think it will be later. Love, M.</add></ab>
                    <note resp="#ebeshero">Indeed, <persName>Warren Moritz Behrend</persName> would be born six days later on March 14, 1909. We conjecture that Mary Behrend wrote and sent these calendar pages
                    while staying with her family in <placeName>Greenwich, Connecticut</placeName> preparing for the new baby’s arrival.</note>
                </div2>




                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-12"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/march/1909-03-12.jpg">

                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP
                        CALENDAR CO. NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-12">March 12, 1909. <lb/>Friday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#multicolor">
                        <figDesc resp="#acolemanreeves">Drawing of a woman in <rs type="object"
                                >snowshoes</rs> named <persName>Molly</persName> pointing ahead of
                            her. This is along the left-hand side of the page.</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil">
                        <lb/><persName>Molly</persName> on <lb/><rs type="object">snowshoes</rs>
                        <lb/>that <persName>Mr. Weir</persName>
                        <lb/>got. <lb/>Pretty <rs type="object">picture</rs>
                        <lb/>is it not?!</ab>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" place="bottom-right"> Love from
                                <persName>Molly</persName></add></ab>
                </div2>


                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-17"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/march/1909-03-17.jpg">

                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP
                        CALENDAR CO. NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-17">March 17, 1909. <lb/>Wednesday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#brownink">
                        <figDesc resp="#acolemanreeves">
                            <rs type="object">Green Shamrocks</rs> dispersed throughout the paper.
                            Two <rs type="animal">snakes</rs> drawn on the top of the paper. A
                            drawing of the <rs type="location">hammermill center</rs> at the bottom
                            right corner. </figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#brownink">
                        <lb/><persName>ST. Patrick</persName> was a useful saint<lb/> He frightened
                        all the <rs type="animal">snakes</rs> away- <lb/>I wish he'd try his art on
                        smoke <lb/>around <rs type="location">the hammermill</rs> some day! <lb/>is
                        it not?!</ab>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive"><rs type="location"> The Hammermill</rs>
                            is really lucky!</add></ab>
                    <!-- finish trasncribing here -->
                </div2>


                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-23"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/march/1909-03-23.jpg">

                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP
                        CALENDAR CO. NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-23">March 23, 1909. <lb/>Tuesday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#pencil">
                        <figDesc resp="#acolemanreeves">Drawing of <rs type="object">clothes</rs>
                            hanging up to dry.</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil">
                        <lb/>WASHDAY AT <persName>THE BEHREND’S</persName>
                        <lb/>OH, I SAY!<lb/>
                        THAT’S REALLY A VERY<lb/>
                        UNUSUAL DISPLAY!</ab>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" place="bottom-right"> Do you <emph style="underline">still</emph> miss
                            me?</add></ab>
                </div2>



                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-25"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/march/1909-03-25.jpg">

                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP
                        CALENDAR CO. NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-25">March 25, 1909. <lb/>Thursday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#multicolor">
                        <figDesc resp="#ebeshero">A woman looking at flowers, presumably at a <rs type="location"
                                >florist shop</rs>.</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil">
                        <title> <emph style="underline">M.B. AT <persName>LAVER’S</persName></emph>
                        </title>
                        <lb/>"I’LL SEND THE <rs type="object">BILL</rs> TO
                            <persName>ERNST</persName>
                        <lb/> AND TAKE THEM EVERY ONE<lb/>
                        I’LL WATCH HIS FACE &amp; SEE HIM <emph style="underline">SMILE</emph>
                        <lb/>IT WILL BE SUCH JOLLY FUN!" </ab>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" place="top-right"
                                ><persName>Molly</persName> running up a big <rs type="object"
                                >bill</rs>. Poor <persName>Ernst</persName></add></ab>
                    <!-- finish trasncribing here -->
                </div2>

            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
